<br>
Anyways, onto the issue at hand.<br>
<br>
I see your point on that Anywon.  I do think economic targets are fair game in war.  After all, if you hurt the economy, you hurt the ability of the nation to make war.  However, I disagree with your ultimate conclusion that everything is ok in war.<br>
<br>
I think I would use the following criterion.  If someone chooses a target that will cause more personal suffering to innocents while having less of an effect on the opponent to make war, that is terrorism.  For example, if you bomb a university because there are people there who will help your opponent to make war through research or other means, then that would not be terrorism.  If you choose to bomb the university just to hurt innocent people, even though another target nearby would have a greater effect on your enemy to make war, then that would be terrorism.<br>
<br>
I think a war can be fought for moral reasons.  Whether that makes war moral is another issue entirely.  I'm not sure a war can really be moral, as it does involve taking lives.  Maybe it can be, I honestly have trouble deciding.  From a philosophically utilitarian point of view, war can be moral if the net effects are good.  Kant, however, probably wouldn't agree as war requires acts that are intrinsically immoral.  It's really not clear cut.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anywon>Anywon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I can't decide on a title</span><br>  Posts: 838<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/19/03 3:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Terrorism vs Warfare</span><hr size=1> I'll list a few recent examples and ask the individual to decide whether the act is one of warfare, designed to reduce economic capacity ... or one to mindlessly kill unarmed masses and invoke fear.<br>
<br>
Piloting an aircraft heavily laden with fuel into a financial symbol of the world'd wealthiest nation.<br>
<br>
Attacking an aircraft loaded with passengers pursuing trans-national trade.<br>
<br>
Detonating a bomb at a bus stop where military personnel are known to commute to/from.<br>
<br>
Detonating a bomb at a shopping center where people are known to involve in trade (thereby supporting the economy and feed the tax base).<br>
<br>
Firing upon a uniformed member of the opposing military from an unseen vantage point.<br>
<br>
Firing upon a uniformed member of the opposing military while not wearing known military insignia or clothing.<br>
<br>
Firing into a crowd of non-military personnel known to support (via economic means) the opposition.<br>
<br>
Detonating a weapon with the intention of killing no less than 10,000 people -- regardless of nationality or affiliation -- but within the geo-political confines of the opposition's territory.<br>
<br>
Complete elimination of all people who share the same genetic, religious, geographical, or ideological affiliations.<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
As you can see the list can contain extremely heinous acts.  None of them are &quot;terrorism&quot; any more than a threat of a speeding ticket is &quot;terrorism&quot; by law enforcement agencies.  The definition of terrorism should be &quot;anything that uses terror or fear as a method to shape the way a person acts&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 2055<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/19/03 4:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Terrorism vs Warfare</span><hr size=1> How about blowing up a bus with a bunch of 5 year old children?  How can that be justified as militarily necessary?<br>
